    "content": "Muller-Breslau principle is used in analysis of structures for ________.",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "drawing an influence line diagram for any force response in the structure"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "writing the virtual work expression to get the equilibrium equation"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "superposing the load effects to get the total force response in the structure"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "relating the deflection between two points in a member with the curvature diagram in-between&nbsp;"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "<p>The Muller-Breslau principle is used in analysis for the following option :</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option A :</strong> drawing an influence line diagram for any force response in the structure</p>\n\n<p>To elaborate further, the Muller-Breslau principle helps determine the influence lines for various structural responses such as reactions, moments, and shear forces. It states that the influence line for a response function (such as deflection, shear force, or moment) at a given point on a structure is equal to the deflected shape of the structure when a unit displacement corresponding to that response is applied at the point of interest.</p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-2",
    "difficulty": null
  },
